data.title: The Neighbourhood - "Cry Baby"
data.meta_description: Goes for Alt adds next week
data.text:
Post by dm2081 on

This actually isn't bad, much better than the lead single. Not sure how much momentum they have right now, but we will see.

Post by maine on

I like this. I listened to the album and I thought it was overall good, but it didn't have any songs that screamed single material to me. Who knows how they'll do considering "R.I.P. 2 My Youth" flopped pretty badly.

Post by Superundercover on

Well I'm still charting "R.I.P. 2 My Youth" and it should be going to #1 in a few weeks.

Post by Devin on

This actually isn't bad, much better than the lead single. Not sure how much momentum they have right now, but we will see.

Well the label sure is moving quickly on a second single, so I'm guessing they'll be pushing this one moderately hard. I expect it to out-peak "R.I.P. 2 My Youth."

Post by Cody on

To be completely frank I could picture a boy band doing this...that doesn't make it a bad song though.

I could picture a boy band singing "Hit The Ground"

Post by Pipa on

To be completely frank I could picture a boy band doing this...that doesn't make it a bad song though.

I could picture a boy band singing "Hit The Ground"

I could picture a boy band singing the Stuck E---no I can't, that's completely unforgivable.

Post by Daryl the Beryl on

-- 7 THE NEIGHBOURHOOD

WIPED OUT!

COLUMBIA 22,931 --

At least they got a top 10 on the pure album sales chart.

Post by Web on

Gave this a first listen, and I'm not a fan. R.I.P. 2 My Youth is a solid track imo but this is kind of whiny and forgettable. Also lyrics have never been this band's strong suit but they stuck out in a bad way here.

Though I am listening to the album now, and nothing has stuck out as a better single choice yet. (maybe The Beach) Nope, the only song anywhere close to good so far is Greetings From Califournia). I think this album is just too pretentious for me, it's like The Neighbourhood met Lana Del Rey on the way to the studio and let her drown out the record with insufferable blandness.

Post by Lordef†ones on

I don't know about y'all but I absolutely love the album. It's had me vibing for awhile. Maybe it's cause I live on the beach and it has that gothic beach vibe to it that fits my setting it. It's super chill and emotionally resonant.

Post by Daryl the Beryl on

Alternative flopping this is a disgrace. Easily my favourite Craig David song yet.

I don't think it's done yet.... give it time.

Post by Lordef†ones on

Sweater Weather: A-

Afraid: B+

Let It Go: A-

R.I.P. 2 My Youth: A+

Cry Baby: A-

Very sad to see them flop. I loved their new album.

Post by bkeysfan on

The problem with them. They're not good enough for pop and they don't sound alternative at all. I don't mind them but I sort of had to accept that Indy rock is considered alternative now.

Post by Green Baron on

I sort of had to accept that Indy rock is considered alternative now.

Hasn't it always though?

Post by bkeysfan on

Well, I guess I should have said Indy pop.

Pandora is playing this song though on the main station, so it might get people to want to hear it more(on actual radio stations that count toward mediabase).
